<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-03-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-03-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">612.112/74: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-26T13:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1924—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:32
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>106. Foreign Office confirms the issuance of circular dated March 21st by
                            General Director of Customs, the second and third paragraphs of which
                            read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <list>
                                    <item>“[Second.] No form of customs’ duties ordinary,
                                        extraordinary or port, or of penalties or pecuniary
                                        sanctions paid by parties to the rebels will be demanded
                                        again by customs offices.</item>
                                    <item>Third. The period of rebel control of ports shall not be
                                        taken into account in the calculation of legal periods of
                                        any kind.”</item>
                                </list>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>